verses.roman:
tabe sei dui-jane prasāda khāoyāilā
nibhṛte duṅhāre nija-ghare pāṭhāilā

synonyms: tabe—then; sei—to those; dui-jane—two girls; prasāda khāoyāilā—gave prasāda to eat; nibhṛte—without being exposed; duṅhāre—both of them; nija-ghare—their homes; pāṭhāilā—sent.
translation: Then Rāmānanda Rāya fed the two girls sumptuous prasāda and sent them to their homes unexposed.
